Reverse_Engineer_Northwind_Database___15__a_Migrations_Setup_Example
//This is the setup for the Migrations example

/*
a]	*/
	 > Install-Package EntityFramework		/*
b] Connection string in App.config			*/
  <connectionStrings>
    <add name="MigrationDemoTest"
         providerName="System.Data.SqlClient"
         connectionString="Data Source=VMHOMETOWER\SQL14;Initial Catalog=efdemo;Integrated Security=True;Application Name=Callbacks (Dev)"/>
  </connectionStrings>

=DATABASE did not exist!!===================================================================================================
NOTE: this did not work at first b/c the database ("efdemo"), in the <connectionStrings> of the App.Config, was not there	
SO: I decided to use one of the other example projects that had all the POCO already in it to Migrate those to the server.

First I went to the SQL 2014 server, and created the empty database: "efdemo"

a) I then enabled migrations */

	>Enable-Migrations		 
							/*

	That did not work, I googled and found that restarting the solution might help. It did.

b) then tried to migrate the POCO that I got from one of the subsequent examples up to the database, in order to populate it's schema */
	> update-database			/*

c} Then I got a message:		*/
	Unable to update database to match the current model because there are pending changes and automatic migration is disabled. 
	Either write the pending model changes to a code-based migration or enable automatic migration. Set 
	DbMigrationsConfiguration.AutomaticMigrationsEnabled to true to enable automatic migration.
	You can use the Add-Migration command to write the pending model changes to a code-based migration.		/*

d)  I changed the statement below from false to true (File: Configuration.cs, class: Configuration)		*/
        public Configuration()
        {
            AutomaticMigrationsEnabled = true;
        }
 /*
 e) tried again:		*/
 > update-database 		/*
 f) this time it worked, and I now have the schema (tables, etc.) on the Server		*/
 ========================================================================================================================/*

/*
c] Now reverse engineer the POCO	

Right-click on Project => Add => New Item => EntityFramework Reverse POCO Code First Generator
{it will create a .tt file} name it anything you want: efdemo.tt

ERROR in 'Error list'
Severity	Code	Description	Project	File	Line	Suppression State
Error		Running transformation: System.NullReferenceException: Object reference not set to an instance of an object.
   at Microsoft.VisualStudio.TextTemplatingCCDF5314B75E55476F52D9F5819B84B123B17257AC4AC896502BA7B39DEE71B87940BD2E6395439309C52F80355835773D5A2697746EFF518983E74142280D6D.GeneratedTextTransformation.IsSqlCeConnection(DbProviderFactory factory) in C:\DATA\EF\6-exercise-files\MigrationDemo\MigrationDemo\EF.Reverse.POCO.Core.ttinclude:line 560
   at Microsoft.VisualStudio.TextTemplatingCCDF5314B75E55476F52D9F5819B84B123B17257AC4AC896502BA7B39DEE71B87940BD2E6395439309C52F80355835773D5A2697746EFF518983E74142280D6D.GeneratedTextTransformation.TransformText() in C:\DATA\EF\6-exercise-files\MigrationDemo\MigrationDemo\efdemo.tt:line 410	MigrationDemo	C:\DATA\EF\6-exercise-files\MigrationDemo\MigrationDemo\EF.Reverse.POCO.Core.ttinclude	560	

d] made following changes to efdemo.tt */

ConnectionStringName = "MigrationDemoTest";
DbContextName = "Db";

//from:
IncludeExtendedPropertyComments = CommentsStyle.InSummaryBlock;
//to:
IncludeExtendedPropertyComments = CommentsStyle.None;

//from
IncludeComments = CommentsStyle.AtEndOfField;
//to
IncludeComments = CommentsStyle.None;

GenerateSeparateFiles = true;

AddUnitTestingDbContext = false;

//Saved the .tt file and the following files were generated:
//------------------------------------
//EF.Reverse.POCO.Core.ttinclude
//EF.Reverse.POCO.ttinclude
//efdemo.tt

=======================================================================================
/* 
Now to test the process, add a column to a table, then save the .tt file again.
Here is the script to add the column:	*/
USE efdemo
GO

ALTER TABLE engineer_person ADD
    date_added DATETIME NOT NULL DEFAULT GETDATE()
GO

/* Before the script the column was not in the POCO, nor the SQL table, after the script, and re-saving the .tt file
